One third of amphibians face extinction due to climate change and pollution, with 122 species already vanished.
Efforts to protect habitats and breed threatened species are crucial.
The decline in frog populations is alarming, with many facing unknown threats.
Scientists link contamination to intersex frogs and population crashes.
Urgent action is needed to prevent further extinctions.
Land consolidation projects offer hope for environmental sustainability.
Despite challenges, restoration efforts are underway to reclaim land and protect biodiversity.
Collaboration is key to saving amphibians and preserving ecosystems for future generations.
